<h2><a name="incomplete" id="incomplete">Lots of people from my
graduating class are missing. Why aren't they listed?</a></h2>

<p>Either they don't have an e-mail address, they haven't been
added to the Directory, or they asked not to be listed. The first
and second reasons are the most common; since the directory is not
affiliated with GENERIC High School, it relies on Internet
citizens to <a
href="/ghs/add/">submit</a> new alumni
e-mail addresses.</p>

<p>And since this is an <em>Internet Directory</em>, alumni must
have an e-mail address to be listed. If you need a free e-mail
address, check out <a
href="http://mail.yahoo.com/">Yahoo! Mail</a>
or <a
href="http://www.hotmail.com/">Hotmail</a>.</p>

<p>Some people aren't listed in this Directory because they don't
want their e-mail address on a public web site. You might find
those people listed on a password-protected site such as:
Registry at:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.alumni.net/">alumni.net</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.classmates.com/">classmates.com</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Other people may have e-mail addresses but might not have found
the Alumni Internet Directory. You might search for them using an
Internet white pages service:</p>

<ul>
<li><a
href="http://people.yahoo.com/">Yahoo! People
Search</a></li>
</ul>

<p><br><br></p>

<h2><a name="mailings" id="mailings">What are quarterly digests of
the Directory?</a></h2>

<p>Every February, May, August and November I e-mail a copy of the
Directory to all members who request it. I do so because some
people don't visit the website (they may have e-mail but not web
access) and also to remind people to update their info if it has
changed.</p>

<p>If you prefer not to receive quarterly digests of the Directory,
you'll still receive two short e-mails a year to confirm that your
contact information is still current.</p>

